"v.污蔑，玷污 【英】 adj. 污蔑，玷污 (to describe opprobrious terms) 【记】 stigma(耻辱，诋譭) ＋tize 【例】 His prison record stigmatized his parents. 无 【记】stigma, stick 棍，刺 + mark 标记，在身体上刺一个标记，如古代烙在犯人身上的印记，表示耻辱 stigmatize (v.)  1580s, ""to brand or tattoo,"" from Medieval Latin stigmatizare, from Greek stigmatizein, from stigmat-, stem of stigma (see stigma). Meaning ""to blemish"" is from 1610s (figurative), 1630s (literal). Related: Stigmatized; stigmatizing."
